- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of sorting networks and uses a SAT solver to determine their optimality. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper constructs propositional formulas to determine the existence of sorting networks with a given depth. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper uses combinatorial arguments to show the existence of sorting networks with a special form. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) may also be relevant as the paper uses combinatorial arguments and propositional formulas to analyze the structure of sorting networks.
